Nasir el-Rufai, governor of Kaduna state, on Friday, led the governors elected on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) to meet with President Muhammadu Buhari. The meeting was held at the council chambers in the presidential villa in the federal capital territory (FCT). TheCable understands that the agenda of the meeting bordered on the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) policy on the new naira notes. Boss Mustapha, secretary to the government of the federation (SGF), and Ibrahim Gambari, chief of staff, were also in attendance. Below are photos from the meeting.            